# Modal patterns (KubeVirt plugin)

All virtualization modals should use one of four standard types. Each type has a fixed contract for validation, errors, and success behavior.

## Shared building blocks

| Building block | Location | Responsibility |
|----------------|----------|----------------|
| `TabModal` | `src/utils/components/TabModal/TabModal.tsx` | Canonical modal shell: submit, loading, footer errors |
| `TabModalBody` | `src/utils/components/TabModal/components/TabModalBody.tsx` | `ModalBody` + optional `Form` wrapper (`shouldWrapInForm`) |
| `TabModalFooter` | `src/utils/components/TabModal/components/TabModalFooter.tsx` | Footer buttons, loading state, danger `Alert` on error |
| `DeleteModal` | `src/utils/components/DeleteModal/DeleteModal.tsx` | Delete/confirm flows wrapping `TabModal` |
| `BackgroundOperationAlert` | `src/utils/components/TabModal/BackgroundOperationAlert.tsx` | Info alert when work continues after closing the dialog |
| `formatK8sError` | `src/utils/utils/formatK8sError.ts` | Explicit `t('...')` per known API error; unmatched errors shown as-is |
| `getK8sErrorHref` | `src/utils/utils/formatK8sError.ts` | Optional `href` on API errors; `TabModalFooter` renders `ExternalLink` when present |
| `exportUploadStore` | `src/utils/components/ExportModal/exportUploadStore.ts` | Zustand store for in-flight export uploads across modal re-opens |
| Validators | `src/utils/utils/validation.ts` | `validateDNS1123Label`, `validateCronExpression`, etc. |

## 1. Form modal

**Examples:** `DiskModal`, `NetworkInterfaceModal`, `HostnameModal`, `SnapshotModal`, `SaveSearchModal`, `MigrationPolicyCreateModal`, `MountCDROMModal` (select-existing-ISO path)

| Concern | Contract |
|---------|----------|
| Base | `TabModal` with `shouldWrapInForm` |
| Validation | `isDisabled={!isValid}` from react-hook-form or a validation hook |
| Required fields | Inline `validated="error"` after blur when empty (`useRequiredFieldValidation` or RHF) |
| Errors | `TabModal` footer danger `Alert` via `formatK8sError` |
| Success | Default `closeOnSubmit={true}` |

## 2. Confirm / delete modal

**Examples:** `DeleteModal`, `DeleteVMModal`, `EjectCDROMModal`, `RestoreModal`

| Concern | Contract |
|---------|----------|
| Base | `DeleteModal` (wraps `TabModal`) — use directly; do not create thin wrapper modals |
| Validation | None by default; domain-specific options (e.g. optional related-resource delete) live in the modal body |
| Errors | `TabModal` footer via `formatK8sError` |
| Success | Close; optional redirect via `shouldRedirect` |

## 3. Progress / background modal

Use the sub-variant that matches the flow. All variants use `TabModal` with `closeOnSubmit={false}` unless noted.

### 3a. Long-running with progress

**Examples:** `CloneVMModal`, `ExportModal`

| Concern | Contract |
|---------|----------|
| Base | `TabModal` with `closeOnSubmit={false}` |
| Validation | Same as form modal before submit; disabled + loading after submit starts |
| Errors | `TabModal` footer |
| Success | Show progress in body; include `BackgroundOperationAlert` when work continues after close |
| Persistence | Use `exportUploadStore` (or similar) when reopening the modal must resume an in-flight upload |
| Copy | Import `BackgroundOperationAlert` — do not duplicate the string inline |

### 3b. Post-submit confirmation

**Examples:** `AddBootableVolumeModal`

| Concern | Contract |
|---------|----------|
| Base | `TabModal`; `closeOnSubmit` toggles after success (e.g. `closeOnSubmit={!!createdResource}`) |
| Success | `onSuccess` captures result; swap body for a success view (e.g. `CreatedVolumeConfirmation`) |
| Actions | Submit becomes "Close"; cancel may become a destructive undo (e.g. "Delete volume") |
| Close guard | Use `onCancel` for destructive undo (e.g. delete created resource); `onClose` / Close submit only dismiss |

### 3c. Fire-and-forget upload

**Examples:** `AddCDROMModal` (upload path), `MountCDROMModal` (upload path)

| Concern | Contract |
|---------|----------|
| Base | `TabModal` with `shouldWrapInForm`; show `BackgroundOperationAlert` while upload is starting |
| Success | Kick off upload, return promise to parent via `onUploadStarted`; modal may close immediately |
| Parent | Parent watches the upload promise and surfaces completion/errors outside the modal |

## 4. Wizard modal

**Examples:** `VirtualMachineMigrationModal`, `VirtualizationFeaturesWizard`

| Concern | Contract |
|---------|----------|
| Base | PatternFly `Modal` + `Wizard` (or `TabModal` for simple flows) |
| Validation | `isNextDisabled` on each step; `isVisitRequired` on wizard to block sidebar skipping |
| Errors | Inline danger `Alert` on review/final step (consistent placement) |
| Success | Status/completion view, then `onClose` |

## Do not

- Use raw PatternFly `Modal` for new flows — use `TabModal` or extend `DeleteModal`
- Show raw K8s API strings without adding a branch in `formatK8sError` — add an explicit case when a new error is observed
- Leave submit enabled when required fields are missing
- Add confirmation checkboxes to `DeleteModal` unless product requires them — prefer `ConfirmActionMessage` only
- Duplicate delete modals that only wrap `TabModal` + `ConfirmActionMessage` — use `DeleteModal` at the call site
- Duplicate `BackgroundOperationAlert` text inline — import the shared component
- Reimplement `TabModalBody` or `TabModalFooter` — extend `TabModal` props instead
